      <trans-unit id="11125" identifier="5e473efc6328e0df7f4191fb8f3129d1">
        <source>The last parity bit placed is useful because it will always work for both the column and row;
if it doesn't match for both the row and column then you'll have made a mistake with one of the cards, and should go back and check them (try to not make it obvious that you're doing that).</source>
        <target>crwdns11125:0crwdne11125:0</target>
        <note>Context: Paragraph text&#13;
XPath: /p[33]</note>
      </trans-unit>
